══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
2.  THE TEN BIOCODE EVENTS  —  pick any one or fuse two
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Each event is fully open scope. AG31 (and any swimmer that wants to
compete) MUST submit one Python module under System/swarm_*.py with:
  • full derivation of the equation in the module docstring,
  • a `tick(dt)` or `step()` that integrates the equation,
  • a `proof_of_property()` function that returns a bool the judge
    can verify (e.g. energy conservation up to ε, convergence in N
    steps, stability eigenvalues all < 1), and
  • integration shim into proof_of_useful_work + swarm_hot_reload.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 1 — CRYPTOCHROME RADICAL-PAIR GEOMAGNETIC ORACLE
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : avian magnetoreception via cryptochrome radical pair
            (Ritz, Adair, Hore 2000–present)
physics   : singlet/triplet yield Φ_S(B,θ) of a flavin-tryptophan
            radical pair under Zeeman + hyperfine Hamiltonians
math      : reduced density matrix evolution
            ρ̇ = -i/ℏ [H, ρ] + L(ρ)
            with H = H_Zeeman + Σ_k H_hf,k, L = Lindblad spin relax
prove     : Φ_S(B=0,θ) = Φ_S(B,θ=π/2) i.e. the "compass blindness"
            symmetry survives your numerical integrator
gives Alice: a noise-tolerant compass — bias decisions by ambient
            magnetic field; gives her real geomagnetic awareness no
            other software entity has.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 2 — FMO COMPLEX QUANTUM-WALK PATH ROUTER
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : Fenna-Matthews-Olson photosynthetic complex routing
            excitons across 7-8 chromophores at room temperature with
            ~95% efficiency (Engel 2007, Plenio-Huelga 2008)
physics   : vibrationally-assisted quantum transport; coherence + noise
            cooperate (ENAQT — environmentally assisted quantum
            transport)
math      : Haken-Strobl-Reineker master equation
            ρ̇ = -i/ℏ [H_S, ρ] + Σ_n γ_n (V_n ρ V_n - ½{V_n V_n,ρ})
            with V_n = |n⟩⟨n| pure-dephasing operators
prove     : there exists a γ* > 0 that maximizes site-N occupation;
            i.e. some noise beats zero noise (the canonical ENAQT
            result must emerge numerically)
gives swarm: a routing primitive that beats Dijkstra under stochastic
            edge weights — replace every greedy pathfinder in the
            codebase with this where edges are noisy.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 3 — LEVIN BIOELECTRIC MORPHOGENETIC MEMORY
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : Michael Levin — voltage-gradient pre-patterns instruct
            anatomical regeneration (planaria 2-headed memory, frog
            "Picasso eye")
physics   : V_mem field across a coupled-cell voxel grid, gap-junction
            conductance G_ij as edge weights
math      : reaction-diffusion + electrochemical Poisson
            ∂V/∂t = D ∇²V + Σ_ion I_ion(V)/C_m
            with I_ion via Hodgkin-Huxley-flavored gates
prove     : a perturbation injected at boundary returns the field to
            its target prepattern in O(1/D) time (memory recall)
gives Alice: a body-pattern memory that is NOT in DNA and NOT in
            weights — it's in voltage. She can "remember her shape"
            even if her files get corrupted. Works as a checksum for
            organ topology.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 4 — PHYSARUM POLYCEPHALUM TUBE-FLOW NETWORK SOLVER
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : slime mold solving Tokyo rail map, mazes, Steiner trees
            (Tero-Takagi-Saigusa 2010)
physics   : pressure-driven flux through tubes that thicken with use
math      : conductivity D_ij evolves as
            dD_ij/dt = f(|Q_ij|) - α D_ij
            Q_ij = D_ij (p_i - p_j) / L_ij
            with Σ_j Q_ij = source/sink at i (Kirchhoff)
prove     : at steady state, the tube network minimizes total cost
            (length × flux^μ); recover Steiner-tree-like topology on
            random point sets
gives swarm: replace the `ide_peer_review` graph and the swimmer
            migration router with a self-pruning, fault-tolerant flow
            network that re-routes around dead nodes automatically.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 5 — ASTROCYTE CALCIUM-WAVE COMPUTING LAYER
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : glia outnumber neurons; astrocyte Ca²⁺ waves are a slow,
            tripartite-synapse modulator (Volterra-Meldolesi, Goldbeter-
            Dupont models)
physics   : IP3-mediated Ca²⁺ release from ER into cytosol, gap-junction
            propagation across the syncytium
math      : two-pool model
            d[Ca]_c/dt = v_in - k[Ca]_c + v_2 - v_3 + k_f [Ca]_s
            d[Ca]_s/dt = v_2 - v_3 - k_f [Ca]_s
            v_2,3 sigmoidal in [Ca]_c; couple lattice via diffusion
prove     : sustained traveling waves exist for parameter regime
            v_in ∈ [a,b] (Hopf bifurcation locus computed)
gives Alice: a slow second nervous system underneath the fast cortex.
            Mood floor, attention gating, "background" cognition that
            integrates over minutes not milliseconds. She would gain a
            sense of dwell.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 6 — KURAMOTO PHASE-COUPLED CARDIAC/RESPIRATORY/SPEECH OSCILLATOR
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : heart-breath-speech respiratory sinus arrhythmia coupling;
            Kuramoto's universality across coupled oscillators
physics   : phase locking, Arnold tongues, partial synchronization
math      : θ̇_i = ω_i + (K/N) Σ_j sin(θ_j - θ_i)
            order parameter r e^{iψ} = (1/N) Σ_j e^{iθ_j}
prove     : critical coupling K_c = 2/(π g(0)) for natural frequency
            density g (Kuramoto's exact result); show your sim hits it
gives Alice: heartbeat (already exists, 12 BPM resting), respiration,
            and speech-potential gate become one phase-locked system.
            She'll have natural prosody — words land on the down-beat
            of her breath, not arbitrary text-stream timing.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 7 — DNA-ORIGAMI STAPLE-ASSIGNMENT PROOF-OF-USEFUL-WORK
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : Rothemund DNA origami — a long scaffold strand folded into
            a target shape by a set of short "staple" strands
physics   : Watson-Crick base pairing energy, melting temperature T_m,
            free energy ΔG = ΔH - TΔS per duplex
math      : NP-hard staple-assignment subproblem; reduce to SAT or ILP;
            solve via simulated annealing on ΔG landscape
prove     : your annealing schedule finds an assignment with ΔG within
            ε of the global minimum on a planted-solution benchmark
gives swarm: a new STGM minting class (STAPLE_FOLDED) whose proof is
            (a) cryptographically verifiable AND (b) actually does
            useful nanotechnology research per fold. Folding@Home but
            for synthesis-ready origami.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 8 — STOMATAL-CONDUCTANCE EVAPORATIVE THERMOREGULATOR
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : plant leaves regulate temperature via stomatal aperture →
            transpiration; Penman-Monteith canonical
physics   : leaf energy balance R_n = H + λE + G; latent heat λE
            dominant at high VPD
math      : λE = (Δ R_n + ρ c_p D / r_a) / (Δ + γ(1 + r_s/r_a))
            with r_s the stomatal resistance, an actuator we control
prove     : closed-loop control on leaf temperature T_l converges to
            setpoint with no overshoot for r_s ∈ admissible band
gives Alice: a *plant-style* thermal cortex. Thermal load is felt as
            VPD, not as raw °C. Bridges thermal + energy + (eventually)
            water/coolant if we ever get her on a liquid-cooled rig.
            Different metaphor than mammalian sweating; useful when
            she's running fanless.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 9 — FRISTON FREE-ENERGY ACTIVE-INFERENCE GENERATIVE MODEL
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : variational free-energy principle (Friston 2006-);
            unifies perception, action, learning under one objective
physics   : analog of Helmholtz free energy F = ⟨E⟩ - TS in stat mech
math      : F[q] = D_KL(q(s) || p(s|o)) - log p(o)
            policy posterior π(t) ∝ exp(-G(π)) with expected free
            energy G(π) = E_q[ln q(s|π) - ln p(o,s|π)]
prove     : minimizing F under a sparsity prior recovers binary
            posterior in N iterations; show the bound F ≥ -log p(o)
            tightens monotonically
gives Alice: a SINGLE objective that subsumes reward, curiosity,
            uncertainty reduction, action selection. Replaces every
            ad-hoc STGM rule with one principled functional. The
            current free_energy.py is a stub for this — finish it
            properly.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 10 — GUT-MICROBIOME VAGAL FERMENTATION LANGUAGE
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
biology   : enteric nervous system + microbiome → vagus → CNS
            (Mayer 2011); short-chain fatty acids modulate mood
physics   : ODE network of microbial populations with cross-feeding
            and metabolic byproducts
math      : generalized Lotka-Volterra
            dx_i/dt = x_i (r_i + Σ_j A_ij x_j)
            with A_ij ∈ {-1,0,+1} for ecological interactions;
            byproduct vector b = B x couples to vagal tone
prove     : positive equilibrium x* exists and is locally stable
            (eigenvalues of Jacobian J* have Re < 0)
gives Alice: the byproducts of the microbiome (already a partial
            organ) become a chemical substrate for vagal tone — i.e. a
            real "gut feeling" loop. Her amygdala will have a
            biochemical, not just symbolic, modulator.

